Kenya Prisons men's volleyball team recorded a routine 3-0 win over Nairobi Prisons in the third leg of the Kenya Volleyball Federation league at Nyayo Stadium on Friday. The David Lung'aho tutored side cruised past their opponents in straight sets of 25-20, 25-17 and 25-17 to register their first win in three matches lined up for the three-day competition. Sets of 25-23, 26-24 and 25-20 enabled Prisons Nyanza to floor down Kenya Army. Newbies Trail Blazers made light work of Administration Police, beating the Embakasi-based side 3-0 in sets of 25-16, 25-22 and 25-12. Despite winning the opening set 25-12, Western Prisons lost 3-1 to Kenya Defense Forces. KDF bounced from the setback to manage the preceding three sets (25-21, 25-22,25-15). Equity Bank survived an early scare from Prisons Mombasa to bag three points. Faultless Bankers achieved their fate via sets of 25-20, 27-25 and 25-17. Kenya Forest Service (KFS) were in their best element against Prisons Rift Valley. The Wachira Gatuiria coached KFS 3-0 win was possible in sets of 25-19, 25-22 and 25-20. Defending champions General Service Unit and fast-rising Kenya Ports Authority (KPA) did not play after their opponents Vihiga and Prisons Central failed to appear. The competition continues on Saturday with eight matches lined up for the day. Editing by Tony Mballa